com.vector.annotations.publishedapi

Annotation Type PublishedField


  • @Documented
 @Retention(value=CLASS)
 @Target(value=FIELD)
 @PublishedApi(value=CLASS_DEPENDENCY)
public @interface PublishedField
    Indicates that the annotated field is part of an published type (see PublishedApi for more details), which must not be changed in the development without an approval for the breaking change!

    Constant Fields

    A constant field is a final field of primitive type or type String that is initialized with a constant value. This value must not be changed without an approval for the breaking change. With the option constantValueChangesAllowed this check can be disabled (e.g. for Version fields, which change there values every release).

    For Example: 

     
 @PublishedField(constantValueChangesAllowed=true)
 public static final String CONSTANT_STRING = "constantString";
